{"word":"ἔκδικος","slug":"ἔκδικος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔκδικος</b></el> <el>(ἔκ-δῐκος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δίκη'><el>δίκη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without law, lawless, unjust</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>exlex</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-κως</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>maintaining the right, avenging</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}